**I had to give one star to leave a review** This store doesn't deserve one star. We have supported many restaurants and sandwich shops during the MoCo Stay-at-home period, and have a good knowledge of how other delivery places work. I ordered lunch at 11:00am for 1:00pm delivery. At 10 minutes after delivery time, I called the store in Rockville. First I was told that all the deliveries had gone out. Then I was told that they'd called a driver who didn't turn up. No apology. The person on the phone said to give the driver some time to arrive at the store. I told him to cancel my order and to refund my credit card. So far, no refund. I believe in supporting local business, but only when they behave in a business like manner. I do not recommend Potbelly Rockville, and I do not recommend  Doordash.

It was about approximately 9:00am. I was looking for something to eat and noticed this Potbelly Sandwich resturant. I had never been to one before.  As I approached the door, a lady entered before me, so, I thought they were in service. As soon as I entered, a man behind the counter said in a not so friendly tone, "We're closed!" Before I could even react, he said again, "We're closed Sir, turnaround." I can't help but believe that that man would have responded differently had I looked like him. As an 62 year old fully grow man, a simple, "Sorry Sir, we're not open yet, but we will be at ***," would have been appreciated. I didn't need him to tell me to "turn around" as if I were going to rob the place. So, even before I had the chance to sample their menu, I know for a fact that I will not be visiting the Rockville location. It bothered me enough to write this review.

I ordered 2 pizza sandwiches.  The first one I watched him put meatballs on (like the sign says it should have). Then when he makes the second one, he doesn't put meatballs on it.  I said 'you didn't put the meatballs on it'.  He said 'it doesn't come with meatballs' ??????  He just made the SAME sandwich with meatballs.  I was in a hurry, and there was a line,  so I didn't make an issue.   Also, note: if you get your movie tickets at the restaurant,  they charge an additional $4.40 more at the theater if the movie is 3D.

I come here often on weekdays around 7pm. It is ALWAYS understaffed. What this means is when your sandwich comes out of the oven, it gets backed up with a bunch of others and by the time the guy who should have been standing there all along gets back from doing someone else's job, its barely warm. Then when you go to pay, there is noone at the register because that person is making a shake or something for someone, so you stand around waiting. Another negative to being understaffed is there are rarely any cookies, pickles or brownies.  I have been to lots of Potbelly restaurants and this is the only one with these issues. At least the food is the same so I guess if you are really patient, it might still be worth it.
